Boy. How about that wind?

35:03.884 --> 35:05.451
I think a storm is coming.

35:05.494 --> 35:06.669
My hair is frightful.

35:06.713 --> 35:07.801
Make yourself at home.

35:07.844 --> 35:09.585
I'll only be a moment.

35:16.853 --> 35:18.203
Did you hear something?

35:18.246 --> 35:19.334
[thunder crashes]

35:24.861 --> 35:26.211
[thunder rumbling]

35:36.221 --> 35:38.788
You said,
"Make yourself at home."

35:40.050 --> 35:41.269
Scooter, really.

35:41.313 --> 35:43.141
I'm old enough
to be your mother.

35:44.664 --> 35:46.274
You're never too old
to have fun.

35:47.580 --> 35:50.191
Why do you want
to have fun with me?

35:50.235 --> 35:51.975
Let's face it.

35:52.019 --> 35:54.108
I'm not a great beauty.

35:54.152 --> 35:56.066
I'm lonely, okay?

35:56.110 --> 35:58.504
You seem like
you're lonely, too.

36:00.636 --> 36:02.247
Yes.

36:02.290 --> 36:03.987
I am lonely.

36:05.032 --> 36:07.121
And rich.

36:07.165 --> 36:09.993
If having money means
you can't trust anyone,

36:10.037 --> 36:12.518
that you can't accept love
when offered...

36:12.561 --> 36:14.520
then what good is it?

36:17.523 --> 36:19.220
[groaning]

36:19.264 --> 36:21.788
There's no need
to be frightened.

36:21.831 --> 36:23.877
It'll all be over so soon.

36:26.749 --> 36:28.838
I want your last moments
to be serene.

36:28.882 --> 36:31.232
-[groans]
-And beautiful.

36:31.276 --> 36:33.365
-[thunder crashes]
-[gasping]

36:34.844 --> 36:37.934
Oh. Did the lightning
startle you?

36:37.978 --> 36:40.023
I'm so sorry.

36:40.067 --> 36:41.242
[grunts]

36:41.286 --> 36:43.244
[groans]

36:47.379 --> 36:49.076
CATHERINE:
So, you really like me?

36:49.119 --> 36:51.121
SCOOTER:
Of course I do.

36:51.165 --> 36:53.211
You're the nicest person
I've met in this town.

36:53.254 --> 36:56.214
CATHERINE:
I'm not that nice.

36:57.302 --> 36:58.520
SCOOTER:
Come on.

36:58.564 --> 36:59.869
You're a doll.

36:59.913 --> 37:01.567
You treat me like I'm somebody,

37:01.610 --> 37:03.743
and the sweet way
you take care of your dad.

37:03.786 --> 37:05.527
CATHERINE:
Oh, I hate my papa.

37:05.571 --> 37:07.660
Even more since I met you.

37:07.703 --> 37:11.185
You make me remember
everything he took from me.

37:11.229 --> 37:13.361
When I still
had something to offer.

37:24.938 --> 37:27.549
I know what it feels like
to think you've missed the boat.

37:29.377 --> 37:31.901
That it's too late

37:31.945 --> 37:33.468
to get what you want.

37:33.512 --> 37:36.210
Maybe it is.

37:38.212 --> 37:39.866
Or maybe it isn't.

37:47.003 --> 37:49.049
[panting]

37:50.703 --> 37:51.834
â™ª

37:51.878 --> 37:53.880
[thunder crashing]

37:55.795 --> 37:57.623
[breathing heavily]

38:13.508 --> 38:15.336
Bertram.

38:15.380 --> 38:17.033
Alma, what are you doing?

38:17.077 --> 38:18.861
There are two people downstairs.
I don't know who they are.

38:18.905 --> 38:20.515
Why didn't you honk the horn?

38:21.560 --> 38:23.692
I did.
You must just not have heard it.

38:23.736 --> 38:25.433
[gasps] Oh. Is it done?

38:25.477 --> 38:27.174
Yes, his suffering has ended.

38:27.217 --> 38:29.045
Which is more than
can be said for mine.

38:29.089 --> 38:30.656
That old man grabbed me.

38:30.699 --> 38:32.048
Will you stop complaining.

38:32.092 --> 38:33.354
We need to get out of here.
Come on.

38:33.398 --> 38:35.400
[clears throat]

38:41.493 --> 38:44.104
There were two people talking
in the living room earlier.

38:44.147 --> 38:45.584
A man and a woman.

38:47.150 --> 38:48.282
[moaning]

38:48.326 --> 38:50.153
Well, they're not talking now.

38:56.508 --> 38:58.423
[thunder rumbling]

38:59.902 --> 39:01.513
Are they there?

39:01.556 --> 39:02.992
Shh.

39:15.570 --> 39:17.442
Maybe the wind
will distract them.

39:17.485 --> 39:19.922
They don't need any more
distracting. Come on.

